# Engineering Rules

- Prefer standard .NET and ASP.NET Core tooling, project structure, and build/test conventions over custom infrastructure.
- Keep API behavior covered by focused xUnit tests and supporting specs under `features/`.
- Preserve clear boundaries between domain logic, persistence, HTTP endpoints, background processing, and external integrations.
- Keep import behavior deterministic, observable, and safe to retry when possible.
- Verify changes with focused `dotnet test`, build, or integration checks appropriate to the change.
- Before relying on external tools or libraries such as `dotnet`, EF Core, database services, or mocking libraries, verify their invocation contract from primary documentation or local help output.
